{
  "texts": [
    "HIGHT is an ARX-based GFS coordinate with key brightening [55].",
    "XOR and bitwise rotations are the significant operations used.",
    "Three different information pivots are XORed together in the F0 and F1 subfunctions.",
    "The master key and 128 subkeys are used in the array to generate 8 bytes of whitening keys.",
    "In various regions of the internal state, addition and XOR are used simultaneously during key whitening and encryption."
  ]
}